<toc-add-entry name="users">User group</toc-add-entry>

<p>Main meeting place of Russian Debian user group are <a
href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-russian">debian-russian</a> mailing
list and #debian-russian IRC-channel on irc.debian.org. If you want
to ask some questions concerning Debian or Linux in general (questions
about Debian are preferred, though) you can do it there. Please do not
send messages in Russian to <a
href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-user">debian-user</a> and other
non-Russian-speaking Debian mailing lists. Most probably you will not
get the answer you expect. Only two Debian mailing lists are Russian-speaking:
<a href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-russian">debian-russian</a> and <a
href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-l10n-russian">debian-l10n-russian</a>.</p>

<p>The Debian project has Russian <a href="http://www.debian.org.ru/">\
website mirror</a> and <a href="ftp://ftp.chg.ru/pub/Linux/debian/">\
ftp-mirror</a>.</p>

<p>Website <a href="http://debian.linuxrulez.ru">Russian Debian</a> does also
contain a lot of useful information.</p>

<toc-add-entry name="l10n">Localization team</toc-add-entry>

<p><a href="http://l10n-russian.alioth.debian.org">Localization team</a>
is responsible for localization of software included in Debian. Its main
mailing list is <a
href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-l10n-russian">debian-l10n-russian</a>.
Currently the main task of localization team is the localization of
new installer of the next Debian release (codename sarge), but the final
goal is of course localization of the whole system. Coordinator of the
localization team is Nikolai Prokoschenko &lt;<email
"nikolai@prokoschenko.de">&gt;.</p>

